Deceased","1207–Female":"1207–Deceased","1207–1301":"1207–1301","1227–Male":"1227–Deceased","1180–Male":"1180–Deceased","1180–Female":"1180–Deceased","1227":"1227","1301":"1301","about 1227":"about 1227","about 1200":"about 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fryar","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Friar   (see   Freer   1)."],"variants":[{"name":"Friar","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Freer  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Fryar was born in 1207, in Scotland, her father, Father of Elizabeth Fryar, was 28 and her mother, Mother of Elizabeth Fryar, was 28. She married Thomas Richard Thompson I about 1227, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1207–":"1207–Surnud","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1207–1301":"1207–1301","1227–Male":"1227–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1227":"1227","1301":"1301","about 1227":"umbes 1227","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1207–":"1207–Kuollut","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1207–1301":"1207–1301","1227–Male":"1227–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1227":"1227","1301":"1301","about 1227":"noin 1227","about 1200":"noin 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1207–":"1207–Décédée","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1207–1301":"1207–1301","1227–Male":"1227–Décédé","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1227":"1227","1301":"1301","about 1227":"environ 1227","about 1200":"environ 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Elizabeth Fryar est née en 1207, à Écosse, son père, Father of Elizabeth Fryar, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Mother of Elizabeth Fryar, avait 28 ans. Elle a épousé Thomas Richard Thompson I environ 1227, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale, et a été enterrée à Écosse."},"de":{"1207–":"1207–Verstorben","1207–Female":"1207–Verstorben","1207–1301":"1207–1301","1227–Male":"1227–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1180–Female":"1180–Verstorben","1227":"1227","1301":"1301","about 1227":"um 1227","about 1200":"um 1200","1207":"1207","1180":"1180","Scotland":"Scotland","lifeSummary":"Als Elizabeth Fryar 1207 in Scotland geboren wurde, war ihr Vater Father of Elizabeth Fryar 28 und ihre Mutter Mother of Elizabeth Fryar 28. Sie hat um 1227 in Scotland Thomas Richard Thompson I geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in ihrem Geburtsort und wurde in Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"1207–":"1207–Desede","1207–Female":"1207–Desede","1207–130